HEALDTON OIL & GAS COMPANY v. Acel C. ALEXANDER, Collector. No. 571. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. April 12, 1932. John E. Hughes, of New York City, for appellant. Herbert K. Hyde, U.. S. Atty., of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges, and POLLOCK, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed April 12, 1932, for want of bill of exceptions.
